				\begin{document} $$ \begin{array}{lll} Q_{\text{loss}} &= \quad ((\geq, 0.20, =, \text{loss}), & (\leq, 0.10, =, \text{gain})), \\ Q_{\text{gain}} &= \quad ((\geq, 0.20, =, \text{gain}), & (\leq, 0.10, =, \text{loss})). \end{array} $$ \end{document}Qloss=((≥,0.20,=,loss),(≤,0.10,=,gain)),Qgain=((≥,0.20,=,gain),(≤,0.10,=,loss)).

In some cases, one can tighten the thresholds in the query in order to achieve more precise results. If we use the query \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
